# 🛡️ Aegis — Complete Project Guide

> **End-to-end explanation of how the project works, how to use it, and how to present it to anyone.**

---

## 1. What is Aegis?

Aegis is a **Customer Support Ticket System** — a web application where customers can raise support issues (called "tickets"), and support agents can respond, track, and resolve them. An admin oversees everything.

### Real-World Analogy
Think of it like a **hospital reception desk**:
- **Customer** = Patient who comes with a problem
- **Ticket** = The complaint slip they fill out
- **Agent** = The doctor assigned to handle the case
- **Admin** = The hospital manager who assigns doctors and monitors everything
- **Chat** = The conversation between patient and doctor
- **Status** = Whether the case is "waiting", "being treated", or "resolved"

### Where is This Used?
| Company | What They Use It For |
|---------|---------------------|
| Zendesk, Freshdesk | Customer support for SaaS products |
| Jira Service Desk | IT help desk for employees |
| Intercom | In-app customer messaging |
| Any e-commerce | Handling refunds, order issues, complaints |

Aegis is a **self-hosted alternative** to all of these.

---

## 2. The Three User Roles

```mermaid
graph LR
  C["👤 Customer"] -->|Creates tickets & chats| T["🎫 Ticket"]
  A["🛡️ Agent"] -->|Responds & resolves| T
  AD["👑 Admin"] -->|Assigns, manages, monitors| T
  AD -->|Manages| C
  AD -->|Manages| A
```

### 👤 Customer (Regular User)
**Who**: Any person using your product/service who needs help.

**What they can do**:
- Register an account
- Create support tickets (describe their problem)
- Chat with the assigned agent in real-time
- Track the status of their tickets (Open → In Progress → Resolved → Closed)
- View only **their own** tickets

---

### 🛡️ Agent (Support Staff)
**Who**: Your company's support team members.

**What they can do**:
- See tickets assigned to them + unassigned tickets
- Reply to customer tickets via real-time chat
- Change ticket status (Open → In Progress → Resolved → Closed)
- View ticket details (priority, category, tags)
- They **cannot** assign tickets to others or manage users

---

### 👑 Admin (Manager)
**Who**: Team lead or system administrator.

**What they can do**:
- See **all** tickets across the system
- Assign tickets to specific agents
- Change any ticket's status
- View full analytics (total tickets, open/resolved counts, category breakdown)
- Manage users (change anyone's role: customer ↔ agent ↔ admin)
- Delete tickets

---

## 3. End-to-End User Journey

### Step 1: Customer Registers
```
Customer opens http://localhost:5173
  → Clicks "Create account"
  → Fills: Name, Email, Password
  → System creates account with role "customer"
  → Redirected to Dashboard
```

### Step 2: Customer Creates a Ticket
```
Dashboard → Clicks "+ Raise a Ticket"
  → Fills the form:
      Title:       "My payment failed but money was deducted"
      Description: "I tried to pay ₹999 for the Growth plan but..."
      Priority:    Urgent
      Category:    Billing
  → Clicks "Create Ticket"
  → Ticket gets ID: TKT-1004 (auto-generated)
  → Status: Open
  → Assigned To: Nobody (yet)
```

### Step 3: Admin Sees the New Ticket
```
Admin logs in → Dashboard shows updated stats
  → Goes to Admin Panel → "All Tickets" tab
  → Sees TKT-1004 (Urgent, Billing, Open)
  → Assigns it to "Aegis Agent" from the dropdown
  → Status auto-changes to "In Progress"
```

### Step 4: Agent Responds via Chat
```
Agent logs in → Sees TKT-1004 in their ticket list
  → Clicks on it → Opens Ticket Detail page
  → LEFT SIDE: Chat panel
      Sees the original description
      Types: "Hi, I can see the failed transaction. Let me check with billing."
      → Clicks Send
  → Message appears in real-time (via Socket.io)
```

### Step 5: Customer Gets the Reply Instantly
```
Customer is on the same ticket page
  → Sees agent's message appear instantly (no page refresh!)
  → Typing indicator shows "Aegis Agent is typing..."
  → Customer replies: "Thank you! Please refund to my bank account."
```

### Step 6: Agent Resolves the Ticket
```
Agent → Right side panel → Changes Status dropdown to "Resolved"
  → Ticket status updates instantly
  → resolvedAt timestamp is recorded
```

### Step 7: Admin Reviews Analytics
```
Admin → Admin Panel → Overview tab
  → Sees:
      Total Tickets: 4
      Open: 0
      Resolved: 2
      Urgent: 1
  → Category chart: Billing 50%, Technical 25%, General 25%
  → Priority chart: visual bars for each priority level
```

