## 4. Technical Architecture (For Developers)

### Tech Stack Overview

| Layer | Technology | Purpose |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| **Frontend** | React 18 + Vite | UI rendering, routing, state management |
| **Styling** | Tailwind CSS | Dark theme, responsive design |
| **Animations** | Framer Motion | Page transitions, hover effects |
| **HTTP Client** | Axios | API calls with JWT interceptors |
| **Real-time** | Socket.io Client | Live chat, typing indicators |
| **Backend** | Express.js | REST API server |
| **Database** | MongoDB + Mongoose | Data storage with schemas |
| **Auth** | JWT + bcrypt | Secure login, password hashing |
| **Real-time Server** | Socket.io | WebSocket connections for chat |

### How Data Flows

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Customer Browser
    participant R as React App
    participant AX as Axios Instance
    participant API as Express API
    participant MW as Auth Middleware
    participant DB as MongoDB
    participant SO as Socket.io

    Note over C,R: 1. Login Flow
    C->>R: Enters email + password
    R->>AX: POST /api/auth/login
    AX->>API: Request with credentials
    API->>DB: Find user, compare bcrypt hash
    DB-->>API: User found
    API-->>AX: { token, user }
    AX-->>R: Store token in localStorage
    R-->>C: Redirect to Dashboard

    Note over C,R: 2. Create Ticket Flow
    C->>R: Fills ticket form, clicks Create
    R->>AX: POST /api/tickets (with JWT)
    AX->>API: Request
    API->>MW: Verify JWT → attach req.user
    MW->>DB: Counter.findOneAndUpdate (TKT-1005)
    MW->>DB: Ticket.create()
    DB-->>API: New ticket
    API-->>R: { success: true, data: ticket }
    R-->>C: Show ticket in list

    Note over C,SO: 3. Real-time Chat Flow
    C->>SO: socket.emit("join_ticket", {ticketId})
    SO->>SO: socket.join(ticketId) room
    C->>SO: socket.emit("send_message", {content})
    SO->>DB: Message.create()
    SO->>SO: io.to(ticketId).emit("receive_message")
    SO-->>C: All users in room see the message
```

### Database Schema Relationships

```mermaid
erDiagram
    USER ||--o{ TICKET : "creates"
    USER ||--o{ TICKET : "assigned to"
    USER ||--o{ MESSAGE : "sends"
    TICKET ||--o{ MESSAGE : "has"
    COUNTER ||--|| TICKET : "generates ID for"

    USER {
        string name
        string email
        string password_hash
        enum role "customer|agent|admin"
        boolean isActive
    }

    TICKET {
        string ticketId "TKT-1001"
        string title
        string description
        enum status "open|in-progress|resolved|closed"
        enum priority "low|medium|high|urgent"
        enum category "billing|technical|general|other"
        ref createdBy "→ User"
        ref assignedTo "→ User"
    }

    MESSAGE {
        ref ticketId "→ Ticket"
        ref sender "→ User"
        string content
        boolean isInternal
        date createdAt
    }

    COUNTER {
        string name "ticketId"
        number value "1004"
    }
```

### Folder Structure Explained

```
server/
├── config/db.js           → MongoDB connection (runs once on startup)
├── constants/roles.js     → "customer", "agent", "admin" (no magic strings)
├── models/                → 4 Mongoose schemas (data shape)
├── middleware/
│   ├── authMiddleware.js   → Reads JWT from header → attaches user to request
│   ├── roleMiddleware.js   → Checks if user's role is allowed
│   └── errorMiddleware.js  → Catches all errors → sends clean JSON
├── controllers/            → Business logic (what to do with the request)
├── routes/                 → URL mapping (which controller handles which URL)
├── socket.js              → WebSocket events for real-time chat
├── seed.js                → Populates DB with demo data
└── server.js              → Glues everything together

client/src/
├── api/axiosInstance.js    → HTTP client (auto-attaches JWT to every request)
├── context/AuthContext.jsx → Global auth state (who is logged in?)
├── hooks/useSocket.js      → Socket.io connection (for real-time features)
├── components/             → Reusable UI pieces (Logo, Badges, Table, etc.)
├── pages/                  → Full page views (Login, Dashboard, etc.)
├── utils/helpers.js        → Utility functions (date format, colors, etc.)
├── App.jsx                → Route definitions + layout
└── main.jsx               → React entry point
```

### Security Architecture

```
Request Flow:
  Browser → Axios (adds "Authorization: Bearer <JWT>") → Express

Server Verification:
  1. authMiddleware.js extracts the token
  2. jwt.verify() checks if it's valid and not expired
  3. Finds the user in DB, checks isActive
  4. Attaches user info to req.user
  5. roleMiddleware.js checks if req.user.role is allowed

Password Security:
  - Passwords are NEVER stored as plain text
  - bcrypt hashes with salt (12 rounds)
  - Even if database is stolen, passwords can't be read

Socket.io Security:
  - JWT is sent during handshake (connection)
  - Invalid token → connection rejected immediately
```

