## 8. How to Run & Use the Project

### Prerequisites
- **Node.js** (v18+)
- **MongoDB** running locally on port 27017 (or MongoDB Atlas URI)

### Setup Commands
```bash
# 1. Clone/navigate to the project
cd "d:\javascript\Cutomer Support Ticket System"

# 2. Install server dependencies
cd server
npm install

# 3. Seed the database with demo data
node seed.js

# 4. Start the backend server (stays running)
node server.js
# Output: 🛡️ Aegis Server running on port 5000

# 5. Open a NEW terminal, install client dependencies
cd client
npm install

# 6. Start the frontend dev server
npm run dev
# Output: Local: http://localhost:5173/
```

### Using the App
1. Open **http://localhost:5173** in your browser
2. Click **"Create account"** to register as a new customer
3. Or use seeded accounts for testing:
   - Admin: `admin@aegis.com` / `admin123`
   - Agent: `agent@aegis.com` / `agent123`
   - Customer: `customer@aegis.com` / `customer123`

### Key Pages
| URL | Page | Who Can Access |
|-----|------|---------------|
| `/login` | Sign in | Public |
| `/register` | Create account | Public |
| `/pricing` | Pricing plans | Public |
| `/dashboard` | Stats overview | All logged-in users |
| `/tickets` | Ticket list | All logged-in users |
| `/tickets/:id` | Ticket chat + details | All logged-in users |
| `/admin` | Control center | Admin only |

